summary: This is a series of emails from February 2021 between FBI agents in New York and Denver coordinating a video interview with a victim (referred to as 'M=') of Jeffrey Epstein. The emails discuss scheduling, the use of Webex, and the victim's request for a trauma-focused therapist.

persons.name: Alicia
persons.context: An FBI agent based in Denver (DN) coordinating contact and scheduling for an interview with an Epstein victim.

connections.description: Alicia, an FBI agent, is coordinating contact and scheduling an interview with victim M=.

events.title: Video interview coordination
events.description: FBI agents coordinate to conduct a video interview via Webex with an Epstein victim.

events.title: Contact made with victim
events.description: After several attempts, FBI agents successfully made contact with victim M= and scheduled an interview for the following morning.

keyFacts: An Epstein victim, referred to as 'M=', resurfaced in early 2021 and was requesting a trauma-focused therapist.
FBI agents from New York and Denver were coordinating a video interview with the victim using Webex.
The correspondence indicates ongoing investigative activity related to Epstein victims well after Epstein's death in 2019.
